# S01-T05: Vercel Config

## Objective
Create `vercel.json` with SPA fallback, push to GitHub, connect to Vercel,
and verify a live empty-shell deployment.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `vercel.json` present with SPA rewrite rule.
- GitHub repo created and pushed.
- Vercel project connected and deployed successfully.
- Live URL opens without 404.

## Steps
1. Create `vercel.json` at project root:
   `{ "rewrites": [{ "source": "/((?!api/).*)", "destination": "/index.html" }] }`.
2. Verify `vite.config.ts` build output is `dist/` (Vercel default, no override needed).
3. Repo already exists: `https://github.com/denistka/musecool.git` (account: denistka@gmail.com).
   Confirm remote is set: `git remote -v`. If not: `git remote add origin https://github.com/denistka/musecool.git`.
4. `git push -u origin main`.
5. Import project to Vercel using denistka@gmail.com account: Framework = Vite, root = `/`, output dir = `dist`.
6. Trigger deploy, confirm URL is live.
7. Note deploy URL in `project.config.yml` under `context.deploy_url`.
